.TH LOOTSHEET-SERVE-TOKEN 1 "Mar 2026" "LootSheet" "LootSheet Manual"
.SH NAME
lootsheet-serve-token \\- Print the server bearer token
.SH SYNOPSIS
lootsheet serve token [flags]
.SH DESCRIPTION
LootSheet CLI

Usage:
  lootsheet serve token

Prints the server bearer token to stdout. Generates a new token if one does
not exist yet. Useful for retrieving the token from a headless or detached
server (e.g. Docker).

Examples:
  lootsheet serve token
  docker exec lootsheet /lootsheet serve token
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
-h, --help
help for token
.SH SEE ALSO
lootsheet-serve(1)
